<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911223-0052</DOCNO><DOCID>911223-0052.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sun Alliance Group PLC:   Insurer Expects Big Loss   On Part of U.K. Business</HL><DATE>12/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   I.REC U.SUN</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)FULL LINE INSURANCE (INF)INSURANCE (INS)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)ITALY (ITA)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Sun Alliance Group PLC, Britain's largest general businessinsurer, said it expects an underwriting loss in its U.K.mortgage indemnity business of #320 million ($587.7 million)in 1991.   The insurer added that in view of the scale of themortgage indemnity loss and the slow pace of non-lifeinsurance markets world-wide, &quot;it must be anticipated thatthe group's 1991 pretax loss will be significantly worse&quot;than in 1990.</LP><TEXT>   Sun Alliance posted a 1990 pretax loss of #181 million.For the first half of this year, it reported a loss of #114million, which compared with a #119 million loss the yearearlier.   The company said it expects to report its 1991 resultsduring the first week of April, but decided to publish apreliminary estimate of the mortgage indemnity loss becauseof the scale of the loss expected.</TEXT></DOC>